#Python with Bottle

https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-deploy-python-web-applications-with-the-bottle-micro-framework-on-ubuntu-14-04

commands
> cd /home/rabih/code_deploy/python-app
> virtualenv --no-site-packages venv
(python3 -m venv env , in Python 3)
> source venv/bin/activate
> pip install bottle
>  nano code/hello.py

# file contents
   from bottle import route, run

@route('/hello')
def hello():
    return "<h1>Hello World!</h1>"

run(host='0.0.0.0', port=8095)

# run the web app
> python code/hello.py

> access the page
http://vps291878.ovh.net:8095/hello



